

Brian C. Wilhite wrote a series of papers on quasar variability (~complete list given below)
and here we aim to reproduce, and build-on, some of that work.




2009astro2010S.329W 2009
Time Domain Research in Astronomy
Wang, Lifan; Cui, Xiangqun; Lamb, Don and 15 more

2008MNRAS.383.1232W 2008/01 cited: 75
On the variability of quasars: a link between the Eddington ratio and optical variability?
Wilhite, Brian C.; Brunner, Robert J.; Grier, Catherine J. and 2 more

2007ApJ...669..791W 2007/11 cited: 14
The Effect of Variability on the Estimation of Quasar Black Hole Masses
Wilhite, Brian C.; Brunner, Robert J.; Schneider, Donald P. and 1 more

2007ApJ...656...73L 2007/02 cited: 82
Broad Absorption Line Variability in Repeat Quasar Observations from the Sloan Digital Sky Survey
Lundgren, Britt F.; Wilhite, Brian C.; Brunner, Robert J. and 5 more

2006ApJ...642...87P 2006/05 cited: 66
Characteristic QSO Accretion Disk Temperatures from Spectroscopic Continuum Variability
Pereyra, Nicolas A.; Vanden Berk, Daniel E.; Turnshek, David A. and 5 more

2006ApJ...641...78W 2006/04 cited: 24
Spectral Variability of Quasars in the Sloan Digital Sky Survey. II. The C IV Line
Wilhite, Brian C.; Vanden Berk, Daniel E.; Brunner, Robert J. and 1 more

2006AJ....131.1923R 2006/04 cited: 23
A Synoptic Multiwavelength Analysis of a Large Quasar Sample
Rengstorf, A. W.; Brunner, R. J.; Wilhite, B. C.

2005ApJ...633..638W 2005/11 cited: 99
Spectral Variability of Quasars in the Sloan Digital Sky Survey. I. Wavelength Dependence
Wilhite, Brian C.; Vanden Berk, Daniel E.; Kron, Richard G. and 5 more

2004PhDT........11W 2004/08
Spectral variability of quasars in the Sloan Digital Sky Survey
Wilhite, Brian C.

2004ASPC..311..385W 2004/06
Optical/UV Quasar Continuum Variability: Time Lag, Luminosity, Wavelength, Redshift, Radio, X-Ray, and BAL Dependence
Wilhite, B.; vanden Berk, D.; Kron, R.

2004ApJ...601..692V 2004/02 cited: 295
The Ensemble Photometric Variability of ~25,000 Quasars in the Sloan Digital Sky Survey
Vanden Berk, Daniel E.; Wilhite, Brian C.; Kron, Richard G. and 11 more

2002ApJ...576..673V 2002/09 cited: 26
SDSS J124602.54 + 011318.8: A Highly Luminous Optical Transient at z = 0.385
Vanden Berk, Daniel E.; Lee, Brian C.; Wilhite, Brian C. and 30 more

